description: From French caracal, from Ottoman Turkish قره‌قولاق‎ (kara-kulak, literally “black ear”), a calque of Persian سیاه‌گوش‎ (siyâh-guš). Compare modern Turkish karakulak.

entries.meaning: A type of cat native to Southern Africa, West Asia, and parts of Central and South Asia, Caracal caracal.
